<i>noun</i>: 훈화 [훈ː화], 훈시 [훈ː시], 잔소리 [잔소리] <br>
<ul>
<li><i>noun</i><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>훈화 [훈ː화]</dt><br>
<dd>instruction; preaching; admonition</dd><br>
<dd>교훈이나 가르침을 주는 말을 함. 또는 그런 말.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of giving another a talk that contains instructive contents or moral lessons; or such a talk.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>훈시 [훈ː시]</dt><br>
<dd>1. instruction; direction; order</dd><br>
<dd>윗사람이 아랫사람에게 맡은 일을 처리할 때에 주의할 점을 일러 줌.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of giving an order or request to one's subordinate regarding matters that require attention when handling one's own mission.</dd><br>
<dd>2. lesson; preaching; teaching</dd><br>
<dd>가르치거나 타이름.</dd><br>
<dd>An act of teaching or persuading another.</dd><br>
<dt><span>&#8227;&nbsp;</span>잔소리 [잔소리]</dt><br>
<dd>1. useless talk; idle talk</dd><br>
<dd>쓸데없이 자질구레한 말을 늘어놓음. 또는 그 말.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of talking about trifling matters uselessly; such talk.</dd><br>
<dd>2. nitpicking; preaching; scolding</dd><br>
<dd>필요 이상으로 듣기 싫은 말을 하며 꾸짖거나 참견함. 또는 그런 말.</dd><br>
<dd>The act of rebuking someone or interfering in his/her affair while saying unnecessary things that he/she does not want to hear; such words.</dd><br>
</li>
</ul>